        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2022-09-27 11:19:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> > Patch Set 1:\n> > \n> > Please explain why we need this dependency. Are they not pulled in from policy-common?\n> \n> Hi Liam, Without adding kafka.clients dependency, ClassNotFoundException's are observed for all org.apache.kafka.clients classes while changing configuration to use Kafka instead of Dmaap.\n> \n> Exception in thread \"main\" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: org/apache/kafka/clients/consumer/KafkaConsumer\n> \tat org.onap.policy.common.endpoints.event.comm.bus.internal.BusConsumer$KafkaConsumerWrapper.<init>(BusConsumer.java:287)\n> \t...\n> Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.kafka.clients.consumer.KafkaConsumer\n> \tat java.base/jdk.internal.loader.BuiltinClassLoader.loadClass(BuiltinClassLoader.java:581)\n> \tat java.base/jdk.internal.loader.ClassLoaders$AppClassLoader.loadClass(ClassLoaders.java:178)\n> \tat java.base/java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(ClassLoader.java:521)",
